HEADWORD: malabar kino
<hw>malabar kino</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The reddish or black juice or
resin from certain trees of the genus <gen>Pterocarpus</gen>, used in
medicine and tanning etc.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> East India kino, kino gum.</syn>⟦br⟧
